Name: BDX
OwnedComment: The largest diameter of the body of a Tool Item.

Name: LBX
OwnedComment: The distance measured along the X axis from that point of the item closest to the workpiece, including the Cutting Item for a Tool Item but excluding a protruding locking mechanism for an Adaptive Item, to either the front of the flange on a flanged body or the beginning of the connection interface feature on the machine side for cylindrical or prismatic shanks.

Name: APMX
OwnedComment: The maximum engagement of the cutting edge or edges with the workpiece measured perpendicular to the feed motion.

Name: DC
OwnedComment: The maximum diameter of a circle on which the defined point Pk of each of the master inserts is located on a Tool Item. The normal of the machined peripheral surface points towards the axis of the Cutting Tool.

Name: DF
OwnedComment: The dimension between two parallel tangents on the outside edge of a flange.

Name: OAL
OwnedComment: The largest length dimension of the Cutting Tool including the master insert where applicable.

Name: DMM
OwnedComment: The dimension of the diameter of a cylindrical portion of a Tool Item or an Adaptive Item that can participate in a connection.

Name: H
OwnedComment: The dimension of the height of the shank.

Name: LS
OwnedComment: The dimension of the length of the shank.

Name: LUX
OwnedComment: Maximum length of a Cutting Tool that can be used in a particular cutting operation including the non-cutting portions of the tool.

Name: LPR
OwnedComment: The dimension from the yz-plane to the furthest point of the Tool Item or Adaptive Item measured in the -X direction.

Name: WT
OwnedComment: The total weight of the Cutting Tool in grams. The force exerted by the mass of the Cutting Tool.

Name: LF
OwnedComment: The distance from the gauge plane or from the end of the shank to the furthest point on the tool, if a gauge plane does not exist, to the cutting reference point determined by the main function of the tool. The {model:CuttingTool} functional length will be the length of the entire tool, not a single Cutting Item. Each {model:CuttingItem} can have an independent {model:FunctionalLength} represented in its measurements.

Name: CRP
OwnedComment: The theoretical sharp point of the Cutting Tool from which the major functional dimensions are taken.

Name: L
OwnedComment: The theoretical length of the cutting edge of a Cutting Item over sharp corners.

Name: DRVA
OwnedComment: Angle between the driving mechanism locator on a Tool Item and the main cutting edge.

Name: DF
OwnedComment: The dimension between two parallel tangents on the outside edge of a flange.

Name: WF
OwnedComment: The distance between the cutting reference point and the rear backing surface of a turning tool or the axis of a boring bar.

Name: IC
OwnedComment: The diameter of a circle to which all edges of a equilateral and round regular insert are tangential.

Name: SIG
OwnedComment: The angle between the major cutting edge and the same cutting edge rotated by 180 degrees about the tool axis.

Name: KAPR
OwnedComment: The angle between the tool cutting edge plane and the tool feed plane measured in a plane parallel the xy-plane.

Name: PSIR
OwnedComment: The angle between the tool cutting edge plane and a plane perpendicular to the tool feed plane measured in a plane parallel the xy-plane.

Name: N/A
OwnedComment: The angle of the tool with respect to the workpiece for a given process. The value is application specific.

Name: BS
OwnedComment: The measure of the length of a wiper edge of a Cutting Item.

Name: SDLx
OwnedComment: The length of a portion of a stepped tool that is related to a corresponding cutting diameter measured from the cutting reference point of that cutting diameter to the point on the next cutting edge at which the diameter starts to change.

Name: STAx
OwnedComment: The angle between a major edge on a step of a stepped tool and the same cutting edge rotated 180 degrees about its tool axis.

Name: DCx
OwnedComment: The diameter of a circle on which the defined point Pk located on this Cutting Tool. The normal of the machined peripheral surface points towards the axis of the Cutting Tool.

Name: HF
OwnedComment: The distance from the basal plane of the Tool Item to the cutting point.

Name: RE
OwnedComment: The nominal radius of a rounded corner measured in the X Y-plane.

Name: LFx
OwnedComment: The distance from the gauge plane or from the end of the shank of the Cutting Tool, if a gauge plane does not exist, to the cutting reference point determined by the main function of the tool. This measurement will be with reference to the Cutting Tool and *MUSTNOT* exist without a Cutting Tool.

Name: BCH
OwnedComment: The flat length of a chamfer.

Name: CHW
OwnedComment: The width of the chamfer.

Name: W1
OwnedComment: W1 is used for the insert width when an inscribed circle diameter is not practical.
